      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "Help me fix the CSS layout issue on my homepage",
      "timestamp": 1783107200000
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user has a CSS layout issue. I need to examine the HTML and CSS files to understand the problem.",
      "model": "gemini-2.5-flash"
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "index.html",
      "output": "<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html>\\n<head>...</head>\\n<body>...</body>\\n</html>",
      "status": "success"
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "styles.css",
      "output": ".container { display: flex; }\\n.header { width: 100%; }",
      "status": "success"
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "I see the issue. The container is using flexbox but the children don't have proper flex properties set.",
      "model": "gemini-2.5-flash"
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "edit",
      "code": ".container { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; }\\n.header { flex: 1 1 100%; }\\n.content { flex: 1 1 300px; }",
      "output": "File updated",
      "status": "success"
    },
    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "I've fixed the CSS layout issue. The problem was that the flex container didn't have proper flex properties for its children. I added `flex-wrap: wrap` and `gap` to the container, and `flex: 1 1 300px` to the content area so it wraps properly on smaller screens.",
      "format": "markdown"
    },
    {
      "type": "side-effect",
      "action": "file_edit",
      "path": "C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\webproject\\styles.css",
